-- EU’s Barnier Mulls Caps on Bank Bonus System, Sueddeutsche Says
-- B y   B r i a n   P a r k i n
-- 2012-02-23T08:52:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-23/eu-s-barnier-mulls-caps-on-bank-bonus-system-sueddeutsche-says.html
European Union Financial Services
Commissioner  Michel Barnier  is assessing rules to cap bank
bonuses across the 27-nation bloc with a view to creating “more
equality and fairness,” the  Sueddeutsche Zeitung  reported.  In an interview, Barnier said he’s exploring ideas
including a rule that would set corridors for lenders’ highest
and lowest pay.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Parkin in Berlin at 
